{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608971","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608971"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:40:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:40:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16059"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16059","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16059"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0.85,0.08,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8750"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66714"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8750"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16059"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52167"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"595"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1501"},{"type":"tags","id":"2968"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7017"},{"type":"tags","id":"10942"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20920"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20923"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22261"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66714","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66714"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents with a painful, red, swollen right breast two weeks after giving birth. She reports difficulty with breastfeeding and has developed a fever of 38.5\u00b0C.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about mastitis is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The common causative organism is a Streptococcus species","Bilateral breast involvement occurs in most cases","Staphylococcus aureus is responsible for most cases","Candida infection is a frequent cause","Antibiotic therapy should be continued for six weeks"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has postpartum mastitis. Whilst this is often due to a build-up of milk, bacterial access through a cracked or damaged nipple can occur and antibiotic therapy is often required. \u003Cstrong\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common cause of mastitis, typically entering through cracked or damaged nipples during breastfeeding. The organism accounts for approximately 80% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStreptococcus species\u003C/strong\u003E can cause mastitis but are less common than Staphylococcus aureus\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBilateral breast involvement\u003C/strong\u003E is uncommon - mastitis typically affects one breast\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECandida infection\u003C/strong\u003E more commonly causes nipple thrush but rarely causes mastitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Esix-week antibiotic course\u003C/strong\u003E is excessive - typical treatment duration is 10-14 days\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETreatment includes appropriate antibiotics (flucloxacillin or cephalexin), continued breastfeeding, supportive measures, and monitoring for abscess formation. If symptoms do not improve within 48 hours of antibiotics, breast ultrasound should be performed to exclude abscess.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Mastitis is most commonly caused by Staphylococcus aureus entering through nipple fissures during breastfeeding","Mastitis presents with breast erythema, tenderness, and systemic symptoms like fever","Failure to respond to antibiotics should raise suspicion for breast abscess formation"],"references":["Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences.","Pevzner M, Dahan A. Mastitis While Breastfeeding: Prevention, the Importance of Proper Treatment, and Potential Complications. J Clin Med. 2020 Jul 22;9(8):2328. doi: 10.3390/jcm9082328. PMID: 32707832; PMCID: PMC7465810.","Blackmon MM, Nguyen H, Mukherji P. Acute Mastitis. [Updated 2023 Jul 21]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK557782/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52167"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16059"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52167","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52167"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T20:13:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T20:14:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8750"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66714"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-